{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"ship-strip-sugar","description":"# S8 — Client walkthrough: self-host Gerrit + rebar review-bot on AWS to gate GitHub\n\n## Why\nA client wants the same setup we built in d251 — a self-hosted Gerrit server combined\nwith the rebar review-bot (which imports the rebar review kernel / `rebar.llm`, the\nsame library the `rebar-mcp` server exposes) — used to GATE commits to a GitHub repo:\nGitHub `main` becomes a read-only mirror that only advances via Gerrit after the\ndeterministic `LLM-Review` vote passes. We need a reproducible, **secret-free**\nwalkthrough that lets a client replicate this code-review-enforcement topology on\ntheir own AWS account + GitHub repo, distilled from the d251 artifacts (Terraform,\ndocker-compose, the Gerrit config scripts, and ADRs 0007-0014).\n\n## What\n- A new client-facing guide `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md` that walks through, end to end:\n  1. **Prerequisites** — AWS account + creds, a GitHub repo + an `Administration: write`\n     token, a domain/DNS zone, Terraform >= 1.10, Anthropic API key.\n  2. **Provision the AWS base** (Terraform `infra/`) — EC2 + EBS + EIP + DNS + IAM +\n     the SSM SecureString parameter contract (`/rebar/prod/*`) — referencing ADR-0012.\n  3. **Deploy Gerrit + the review-bot** (docker-compose behind nginx/TLS) — referencing\n     ADR-0007 (receiver-not-MCP-over-HTTP) + ADR-0008 (SSM->.env secrets).\n  4. **Configure the Gerrit project + `LLM-Review` label + submit requirement** —\n     referencing ADR-0013.\n  5. **Wire the review-bot identity + webhooks + events-log** — referencing ADR-0014\n     (inbound auth) + ADR-0009 (the verdict->label pipe / `code_review_decision` seam).\n  6. **Gerrit -> GitHub replication** (deploy key, non-force) — referencing ADR-0010.\n  7. **Lock the GitHub repo** to the replication identity — referencing ADR-0011 + S6-pre.\n  8. **Verify + operate** — the e2e check, the manual `/rerun`, the kill-switch, rollback.\n  The guide uses the committed `infra/` scripts/config as the source of truth and shows\n  the operator commands; it does NOT duplicate large config inline.\n- **No secrets in committed docs.** All credentials are PLACEHOLDERS sourced from SSM /\n  CI secrets (never literal). The guide explicitly calls out the secret-handling model.\n- **Link from the existing install docs.** Add a link to `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md`\n  from the project's install documentation (README / docs index) as an OPTIONAL /\n  ADVANCED step titled for \"code-review enforcement (self-hosted Gerrit gating GitHub)\".\n\n## Scope\nIn: the `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md` walkthrough, the link from the install docs, and a\nno-secrets verification of all committed documentation. Out: any NEW infrastructure or\ncode (S8 reuses and references the d251 artifacts produced by S1-S7); per-client\ncustomization beyond the walkthrough.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md` exists and is a complete, ordered client walkthrough\n      covering all eight steps above (provision -> deploy -> project/label/submit-req ->\n      bot/webhooks/events-log -> replication -> GitHub lock -> verify/operate), each step\n      referencing the relevant `infra/` artifact(s) and ADR(s).\n- [ ] The new guide and ALL committed documentation in the repo contain NO secrets —\n      only placeholders; credentials are sourced from SSM Parameter Store / CI secrets.\n      Verified by a secret scan over the committed docs (and `infra/`).\n- [ ] `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md` is linked from the existing install docs (README and/or\n      the docs index) as an explicitly OPTIONAL / ADVANCED step for code-review\n      enforcement (self-hosted Gerrit gating GitHub) — discoverable from the normal\n      install path but not required for standard rebar use.\n- [ ] The walkthrough's secret-handling section documents the SSM-SecureString -> ephemeral\n      `.env` model (ADR-0008) and that no credential is ever committed.","id":"1628-ad81-0831-46a2","parent_id":"d251-05e1-eb55-43b2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Client walkthrough: self-host Gerrit + rebar review-bot on AWS to gate GitHub"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782796298205573001,"uuid":"981ff6e4-cfb3-4232-9b3b-4e8f0ee33421"}